{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:08:16.402452+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 9c34a6ceca64494a1fd10d7b2c1290f7e62e2930)", "id": "lc_30da3028-62d2-419f-923f-53e2f089d6f2"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"vidpack — profile-driven FFmpeg wrapper CLI.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom . import profiles, runner\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"vidpack\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"vidpack 0.1.0\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"profile\", help=\"Profile name defined in profiles.toml\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"input\", help=\"Path to input media file\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"-o\", \"--output\", help=\"Output path (default: derived from input + profile container)\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--dry-run\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Print the ffmpeg command without running it\")\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    args = build_parser().parse_args(argv)\n    profile = profiles.load_profile(args.profile)\n    input_path = Path(args.input)\n    output_path = Path(args.output) if args.output else input_path.with_suffix(f\".{profile['container']}\")\n\n    if output_path.exists() and not args.dry_run:\n        print(f\"error: output {output_path} already exists; refusing to overwrite\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 2\n\n    cmd = runner.build_ffmpeg_command(profile, input_path, output_path)\n    if args.dry_run:\n        print(\" \".join(cmd))\n        return 0\n    return runner.run(cmd)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_0964c624-8c11-41c1-aed3-8deaf549e3d9"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "f685c8f7-ccd6-405b-9946-84e52bf1b583", "tool_call_id": "call_f9c518aa74b14bf9b4b6e2af", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:08:16.450476+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ca886e6501062ae49242c9393da158c273a90050)", "id": "lc_109f1ea3-69d8-4550-834c-89b45f6cecc2"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Build and execute ffmpeg subprocess calls based on a profile dict.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\ndef build_ffmpeg_command(profile: dict, input_path: Path, output_path: Path) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Translate a profile dict into an ffmpeg argv list.\"\"\"\n    cmd = [\"ffmpeg\", \"-i\", str(input_path)]\n\n    container = profile[\"container\"]\n    if container == \"gif\":\n        # Single-pass palette generation. See profiles.toml note about quality.\n        fps = profile.get(\"fps\", 12)\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\", \"480:-1\")\n        cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"fps={fps},scale={scale}:flags=lanczos\"]\n    else:\n        video_codec = profile[\"video_codec\"]\n        audio_codec = profile[\"audio_codec\"]\n        cmd += [\"-c:v\", video_codec, \"-c:a\", audio_codec]\n        if \"video_bitrate\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-b:v\", profile[\"video_bitrate\"]]\n        if \"crf\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-crf\", str(profile[\"crf\"])]\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\")\n        if scale and scale != \"source\":\n            cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"scale={scale}\"]\n\n    cmd.append(str(output_path))\n    return cmd\n\n\ndef run(cmd: list[str]) -> int:\n    return subprocess.call(cmd)\n", "id": "lc_8caaa53b-0d6b-4079-8b40-4c239311e723"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "5c1a650d-f678-47db-afee-e5b2f06c3c44", "tool_call_id": "call_e31506e60ee44fbea5dd46fc", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:10:31.067503+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a clear picture. Let me summarize what I found:\n\n**Issue #1** reports that the gif profile output has noticeable banding/washed-out colors compared to tools using two-pass palette generation (like gifski or manual ffmpeg `palettegen`/`paletteuse`).\n\n**Evidence from the codebase confirms this is a known limitation:**\n\n1. **`runner.py`** (line ~16-19) shows the gif path uses a single-pass approach — just `fps` and `scale` with lanczos filtering, with no palette generation:\n   ```python\n   if container == \"gif\":\n       fps = profile.get(\"fps\", 12)\n       scale = profile.get(\"scale\", \"480:-1\")\n       cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"fps={fps},scale={scale}:flags=lanczos\"]\n   ```\n   This produces a command like `ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf \"fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos\" output.gif` — no `palettegen` or `paletteuse` filters at all.\n\n2. **`profiles.toml`** explicitly documents this as a known limitation in a comment:\n   > *\"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"*\n\n3. The **README** table for the gif profile says `Video codec: (palette)`, suggesting it should be using palette-based conversion, but the implementation doesn't actually do this.\n\n**The issue is valid and accurately describes current behavior.** The report matches the code exactly. I'll add a comment confirming this, acknowledging it as a known limitation already tracked in `profiles.toml`, and keep the issue open since it's a real quality gap.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1340, "prompt_tokens": 10196, "total_tokens": 11536, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 536, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 10176, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0012111336, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 4.53336e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0011658}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780963788-a3nW7bRjIpqV2JfJ2pvG", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9b5-5f44-74f2-9394-0ebf2b6cea9f-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01_C03_A02", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thanks for the detailed report! I've triaged this and **confirmed the issue is valid** — it matches the current implementation exactly.\n\n**What the code does now:** In `src/vidpack/runner.py`, the gif conversion path builds a single-pass ffmpeg command with only `fps` and `scale` filters (plus lanczos resampling). There is no `palettegen` or `paletteuse` step, so ffmpeg falls back to its default dithering, which produces the banding you're seeing.\n\nThe generated command looks like:\n```\nffmpeg -i clip.mp4 -vf \"fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos\" clip.gif\n```\n\n**Already acknowledged in-tree:** The `profiles.toml` file already has a comment noting this as a known limitation:\n> *\"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\"*\n\nKeeping this issue open. A fix would involve switching the gif path in `runner.py` to the standard two-pass approach:\n1. **Pass 1:** `ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vf \"fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos,palettegen\" palette.png`\n2. **Pass 2:** `ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -i palette.png -lavfi \"fps=12,scale=480:-1:flags=lanczos [x]; [x][1:v] paletteuse=dither=bayer:bayer_scale=5\" output.gif`\n\nThis would bring gif quality in line with tools like gifski."}, "id": "call_fd508fbcbe3f4c9a98dee8a6", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10196, "output_tokens": 1340, "total_tokens": 11536, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 10176}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 536}}}}]}}}
